Section 1.1: The QEMU Boot Sequence

The 10,000-Foot View

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    QEMU BOOT SEQUENCE                           │
│                                                                 │
│  main() → qemu_init() → machine->init() → creation_done()      │
│       ↓           ↓              ↓              ↓              │
│   Parse args   Build QOM      Create CPUs   Start vCPUs       │
│   Setup QMP    Init devices   Load BIOS     vm_start()        │
│                                                                 │
│  Key Stages:                                                    │
│  1. Command line parsing                                       │
│  2. QOM object creation                                        │
│  3. Machine initialization                                     │
│  4. Device realization                                         │
│  5. Firmware loading                                           │
│  6. CPU initialization                                         │
│  7. VM start                                                   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Detailed Boot Flow

```c
// softmmu/main.c - simplified

int main(int argc, char **argv, char **envp) {
    // 1. Parse command line
    qemu_init(argc, argv);
    
    // 2. Main loop (never returns)
    qemu_main_loop();
    
    return 0;
}

// softmmu/vl.c - qemu_init()

void qemu_init(int argc, char **argv) {
    // 1. Early initialization
    qemu_init_early();
    
    // 2. Parse command line
    qemu_parse_args(argc, argv);
    
    // 3. Create machine
    machine = machine_init(current_machine);
    
    // 4. Create CPUs
    cpu_init(machine);
    
    // 5. Create devices
    device_init(machine);
    
    // 6. Load firmware
    load_firmware(machine);
    
    // 7. Memory initialization
    memory_init(machine);
    
    // 8. Start vCPUs
    qemu_create_cpus();
    
    // 9. VM ready
    creation_done();
}

// softmmu/vl.c - vm_start()

void vm_start(void) {
    // 1. Resume CPUs
    for (CPUState *cpu = first_cpu; cpu; cpu = cpu->next_cpu) {
        cpu_resume(cpu);
    }
    
    // 2. Start event loop
    qemu_system_reset_request();
    
    // 3. Set running state
    vm_state = RUN_STATE_RUNNING;
    
    // 4. Notify listeners
    vm_state_notify(RUN_STATE_RUNNING);
}
```

