Section 1.2: Firmware Boot Process

x86 Reset Vector

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    x86 BOOT SEQUENCE                            │
│                                                                 │
│  1. CPU reset: CS = 0xF000, IP = 0xFFF0                       │
│     → First instruction at 0xFFFF0 (16 bytes)                 │
│                                                                 │
│  2. BIOS (SeaBIOS/OVMF) starts at 0xFFFF0                     │
│     → Jump to 0xF000:0xE05B (BIOS entry)                     │
│                                                                 │
│  3. BIOS initialization:                                      │
│     • Memory detection                                        │
│     • PCI enumeration                                         │
│     • ACPI tables                                             │
│     • Boot device selection                                   │
│                                                                 │
│  4. Load bootloader (GRUB) from MBR                           │
│     → Jumps to 0x7C00                                         │
│                                                                 │
│  5. Bootloader loads kernel                                    │
│     → Jumps to 0x100000 (1MB)                                 │
│                                                                 │
│  6. Kernel starts (vmlinux)                                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

QEMU Firmware Loading

```c
// hw/i386/pc.c

static void pc_memory_init(MachineState *machine) {
    // 1. Create BIOS memory region
    MemoryRegion *bios = g_new(MemoryRegion, 1);
    memory_region_init_rom(bios, NULL, "pc.bios", 0x100000, &error_fatal);
    memory_region_add_subregion(system_memory, 0x100000000 - 0x100000, bios);
    
    // 2. Load BIOS file (SeaBIOS/OVMF)
    char *bios_name = pc_machine->bios_name;
    char *filename = qemu_find_file(QEMU_FILE_TYPE_BIOS, bios_name);
    
    // 3. Read BIOS file into memory
    int fd = open(filename, O_RDONLY);
    read(fd, memory_region_get_ram_ptr(bios), 0x100000);
    close(fd);
    
    // 4. Reset vector at 0xFFFF0
    // BIOS entry point is at 0xFFFF0: jmp far 0xF000:0xE05B
    uint8_t *bios_ptr = memory_region_get_ram_ptr(bios);
    bios_ptr[0xFFFF0] = 0xEA;  // JMP FAR
    bios_ptr[0xFFFF1] = 0x5B;  // IP low
    bios_ptr[0xFFFF2] = 0xE0;  // IP high
    bios_ptr[0xFFFF3] = 0x00;  // CS low
    bios_ptr[0xFFFF4] = 0xF0;  // CS high
}
```

